n%20its%20post%2C%20but%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20keep%20improving%2C%20guided%20by%20experts%20and%20grounded%20in%20responsibility%20to%20the%20people%20who%20use%20our%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20hope%20others%20will%20join%20us%20in%20helping%20make%20sure%20this%20technology%20protects%20people%20at%20their%20most%20vulnerable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20company%20is%20saddened%20by%20Raine's%20passing%20and%20that%20ChatGPT%20includes%20safeguards%20such%20as%20directing%20users%20to%20crisis%20helplines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20these%20safeguards%20work%20best%20in%20common%2C%20short%20exchanges%2C%20we've%20learned%20over%20time%20that%20they%20can%20sometimes%20become%20less%20reliable%20in%20long%20interactions%20where%20parts%20of%20the%20model's%20safety%20training%20may%20degrade%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20OpenAI%20will%20continually%20improve%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b1dd42f-bc7e-415d-84ad-dc9d87d29ee3%5C%22%3EThe%20dark%20side%20of%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20also%20took%20aim%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-gpt-5-agi-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20business%20decisions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20accusing%20the%20company%20of%20prioritizing%20growth%20over%20safety.%20In%20the%20complaint%2C%20Matthew%20and%20Maria%20Raine%20said%20that%20OpenAI%20knew%20that%20new%20features%20in%20the%20GPT-4o%20model%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20memory%2C%20human-like%20empathy%2C%20and%20sycophancy%20%E2%80%94%20could%20endanger%20vulnerable%20users%2C%20but%20released%20them%20anyway%20to%20keep%20up%20in%20the%20AI%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20decision%20had%20two%20results%3A%20OpenAI's%20valuation%20catapulted%20from%20%2486%20billion%20to%20%24300%20billion%2C%20and%20Adam%20Raine%20died%20by%20suicide%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20previously%20said%20in%20an%20April%20blog%20post%20that%20it%20may%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-safety-policy-gpt4-1-employee-criticism-musk-lawsuit-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echange%20its%20safety%20requirements%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20%26quot%3Banother%20frontier%20AI%20developer%20releases%20a%20high-risk%20system%20without%20comparable%20safeguards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20it%20would%20only%20do%20so%20after%20confirming%20the%20risk%20landscape%20had%20changed%2C%20publicly%20acknowledging%20the%20decision%2C%20and%20ensuring%20it%20wouldn't%20meaningfully%20increase%20the%20chance%20of%20severe%20harm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20OpenAI%20rolled%20out%20its%20GPT-4.1%20models%20in%20April%2C%20the%20company%20did%20so%20without%20publishing%20a%20model%20or%20system%20card%20%E2%80%94%20the%20safety%20documentation%20that%20typically%20accompanies%20new%20releases.%20An%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20told%20TechCrunch%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20models%20weren't%20%26quot%3Bfrontier%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20a%20report%20wasn't%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20defended%20OpenAI's%20evolving%20approach%20to%20safety.%20In%20April%2C%20he%20said%20companies%20regularly%20pause%20releases%20over%20safety%20concerns%2C%20but%20acknowledged%20OpenAI%20had%20loosened%20some%20restrictions%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-user-health-safeguards-reminders-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emodel%20behaviour%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20given%20users%20much%20more%20freedom%20on%20what%20we%20would%20traditionally%20think%20about%20as%20speech%20harms%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20really%20d